---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="symbols"
  description="symbols index / hidden archive / fire, fool, serpent, tree of life, mandala, labyrinth, mirror"
>
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="hero-kicker">symbols / archive wing / index</div>
    <h1>symbols</h1>
    <p>
      symbolic forms that carry more than one meaning at once. not fixed definitions,
      but living images that open inward.
    </p>
    <p class="muted">
      this wing gathers recurring images that appear in myth, dream, religion, death,
      transformation, and the deeper life of the psyche.
    </p>
  </section>

  <div class="box">
    <div class="box-title">entry sequence</div>
    <div class="box-body">
      <div class="grid-links">
        <a href="/symbols/fire">
          <span class="link-title">fire</span>
          <span class="link-desc">transformation, destruction, illumination, spirit.</span>
        </a>

        <a href="/symbols/fool">
          <span class="link-title">the fool</span>
          <span class="link-desc">play, paradox, death, innocence, and the cosmic joke.</span>
        </a>

        <a href="/symbols/serpent">
          <span class="link-title">the serpent</span>
          <span class="link-desc">instinct, danger, wisdom, renewal, and hidden power.</span>
        </a>

        <a href="/symbols/tree-of-life">
          <span class="link-title">tree of life</span>
          <span class="link-desc">growth, connection, worlds, structure of being.</span>
        </a>

        <a href="/symbols/mandala">
          <span class="link-title">the mandala</span>
          <span class="link-desc">center, wholeness, order, and the image of the self.</span>
        </a>

        <a href="/symbols/labyrinth">
          <span class="link-title">the labyrinth</span>
          <span class="link-desc">descent, initiation, confusion, center, and return.</span>
        </a>

        <a href="/symbols/mirror">
          <span class="link-title">mirror</span>
          <span class="link-desc">reflection, truth, illusion, self-seeing.</span>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="box">
    <div class="box-title">how to use this wing</div>
    <div class="box-body">
      <p>
        symbols should not be treated like dead dictionary entries. one image can carry
        many layers at once depending on context, dream life, mythic history, and the
        state of the person encountering it.
      </p>
      <p>
        the best way to read this section is slowly. follow the images that pull on you.
        often the symbol that most fascinates you or disturbs you is the one carrying the
        strongest message.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="box">
    <div class="box-title">symbols map</div>
    <div class="box-body">
      <p><a href="/symbols/fire" class="link-blue">fire</a> — transformation, spirit, destruction, illumination</p>
      <p><a href="/symbols/fool" class="link-red">fool</a> — play, paradox, death, reversal</p>
      <p><a href="/symbols/serpent" class="link-green">serpent</a> — instinct, danger, gnosis, rebirth</p>
      <p><a href="/symbols/tree-of-life">tree of life</a> — growth, structure, connection of worlds</p>
      <p><a href="/symbols/mandala">mandala</a> — totality, psychic order, hidden center</p>
      <p><a href="/symbols/labyrinth">labyrinth</a> — wandering, ordeal, center, return</p>
      <p><a href="/symbols/mirror">mirror</a> — reflection, truth, illusion</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="box">
    <div class="box-title">next expansion</div>
    <div class="box-body">
      <p class="muted">
        this wing will keep expanding as the archive grows.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>